# Expressif

This Visual Studio Code extension adds syntax highlighting for **Expressif** expressions, making functions and parameters easier to read and write.

Expressif is a transformation expression language with rich built-in functions and first-class support in Visual Studio Code.

## Features of the extension
Syntax highlighting for Expressif expressions

## Expressif language

### Examples

```
[date]
| next-business-days(2)
| year
```

```
"hello"
| prefix(">> ")
| upper
```

### cheat Sheet

Literals: null, empty, blank, any, value
Operators: Pipe |
Strings:
- "double quotes"
- `backticks`

## Installation

From VSIX
Open Visual Studio Code
Go to Extensions
Click ... (top-right)
Select Install from VSIX...
Choose your .vsix file
File Types

Use one of the following extensions:

- .expr
- .expressif

